- Used stow to manage dotfiles

# Setting up C++ with neovim:

- installed neo vim with:
sudo dnf install -y neovim python3-neovim

- installed jet brains mono fonts with:
sudo dnf install jetbrains-mono-fonts

- installed jet brains mono nerd font with (source: https://discussion.fedoraproject.org/t/maveonair-jetbrains-mono-nerd-fonts/99033):
sudo dnf copr enable maveonair/jetbrains-mono-nerd-fonts
sudo dnf install jetbrains-mono-nerd-fonts jetbrains-mononl-nerd-fonts

- Added NvChad as a default base config for neo vim:
git clone https://github.com/NvChad/NvChad.git ./.config/nvim --depth 1
- run "nvim" -> < then answer No to the question if u want to install default neo vim config >

- You can change the theme in neo vim with "space+t+h"

- Used mason for configuration. ":MasonInstallAll" command in nvim to install everything

- Used lspconfig for lsp server

# Other stuff
- Install tmux plugins with "<prefix key> I"

- Installed "Hack" font



